    {
        "content": "<p>seems the answer is to just use <code>H ⊔ K</code></p>",
        "id": 305278804,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1666326392
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or if you want the underlying set to be definitionally <code>↑H * ↑K</code>, you may use <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/subgroup.copy\">docs#subgroup.copy</a></p>",
        "id": 305278840,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1666326457
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Nice! Using<code>H ⊔ K</code> is sufficient for my purposes, but it is good to know about <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/subgroup.copy\">docs#subgroup.copy</a>.</p>",
